item.title: Hagia Sophia Must Revert to a Mosque, Turkish Court Rules
item.description: President Recep Tayyip Erogan had supported the move, which will turn the sixth-century monument, long a symbol of secularism, back into a place of worship, but he is opposed by the U.S. and others.

item.title: Singapore's Ruling Party Keeps Hold on Power, but Opposition Gains
item.description: Singapore’s ruling party kept its hold on power in national elections, but the opposition made significant gains, capturing the highest number of seats it ever has in the tightly controlled city-state that now faces a recession stemming from the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Trump Dims Hopes for New China Trade Deal
item.description: President Trump said that he is no longer thinking about negotiating a phase-two trade deal with China, saying the relationship between the countries has been badly damaged by the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Bulgaria and Croatia Take Vital Step Toward Adopting Euro
item.description: Bulgaria and Croatia took a big step toward adopting the euro currency, potentially becoming the newest members to the bloc after years of economic crises and shocks.

item.title: Canadian Prime Minister Faces Ethics Questions Over Charity Contract
item.description: Justin Trudeau is facing ethics questions about his government’s decision to grant a contract worth hundreds of millions of dollars to a charity whose events his family members have been paid to speak at.

item.title: Balkan Countries Thought They Had Beaten Back Coronavirus. Now Infections Are Rampant.
item.description: Coronavirus infections are surging in southeastern Europe and some other regions that had initially managed to curb the pandemic, and some governments are facing protests as they restore confinement measures.

item.title: Coronavirus Threatens Syrian Rebel Stronghold
item.description: The novel coronavirus has crept into the last opposition-held territory in Syria, as Russia and China move to restrict an aid corridor that humanitarian groups warn could hamper attempts to contain an outbreak in the besieged area.
